===Etymology===
From {{inh|zh|sit-pro|*r-p(w)am||to freeze; snow}} (provisionally reconstructed) (STEDT).
:Insides Sinitic, {{och-l|凌|tr=*p.rəŋ ~ [r]əŋ}} is cognate with {{och-l|冰|tr=*p.rəŋ}}, {{och-l|雱|tr=*pʰˁaŋ}} "heavy snowfall", {{och-l|霙|*''ʔraŋ''}} "snowflake, sleet", & possibly also {{och-l|凝|tr=[ŋ](r)əŋ}} "to congeal" (STEDT; {{zh-ref|Baxter and Sagart, 2014}});
:Outsides Sinitic, cognate with {{cog|sit-tan-pro|*pam||snow}}, {{cog|sit-jap|jpɣom||to freeze}}, {{m|sit-jap|tɤjpɣom||ice}} (STEDT; {{zh-ref|Zhang, Jacques, and Lai, 2019}}).

Alternatively, {{och-l|冰|tr=*prjəŋ ~ prəŋ?}} and {{och-l|凌|tr=*b-rjəŋ ~ rəŋ}} may be related to {{cog|okz|ប្រិង៑|t=to harden; to solidify}} from {{m|okz|រិង៑|t=to dry up}}, although the meanings are difficult to reconcile ({{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}}).

